subSubSection.paragraph:
On the upper cheekteeth, both the crown morphology and the number and arrangement of the roots are quite unusual. As in the lower cheekteeth, the first and second molar are hypertrophied. The molars progressively decrease in size posteriorly, M1> M2> M3> M4> M5 (
Figs 1C, D
; 
2
).

